<h2>An Unbalanced Economy</h2>
<p>At the end of WWI, farmersâ€™ income began to decrease due to the slowing demand for food during peacetime. Also, factories began having trouble selling everything they produced. This overproduction of goods forced factory owners to slow production and fire or cut the wages of workers. Jobless or with reduced income, many Americans had to cut back on purchases, further reducing sales.</p>
